title: Independent candidate Ihtisham Ali wins PK-61 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Ihtisham Ali has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-61 Mardan-VIII by securing 32,984 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was PML-N’s Jamshaid Khan who bagged 20,645 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 46.29 per cent.
